    id: 23,
    title: "“The Wait”",
    excerpt: "He’s there, / somewhere in his own world, / holding onto the thread of an unfinished love —",
    full: `He’s there,
somewhere in his own world,
holding onto the thread of an unfinished love —
waiting for that love,
perhaps the same one
that once bloomed quietly in my eyes.

And here I am,
still standing at the same crossroad,
where his memories visit me each day,
whisper a few silent words,
and then fade away into the dusk.

They say —
no matter how long you wait for love,
it never truly ends.
It just grows deeper, quieter,
turning into something eternal.

When love is real,
even the attempt to forget
becomes another form of remembering.

I’ve carried his name in every heartbeat,
breathed his presence in every sigh,
and even now, when the wind passes by,
I feel him near —
smiling,
the same soul
my heart still beats for.

Strange, isn’t it?
He lives beneath another sky,
in another time,
while I gaze at the same stars,
hoping our unspoken prayers
still collide somewhere in between.

Love never fades —
it just transcends words,
leaving behind a tenderness
that moistens the eyes
and soothes the soul... 💫🌹`,
