    id: 24,
    title: "“Who Loves the Most?”",
    excerpt: "Male love and female love — / two hearts that feel the same storm differently. / A man’s love hides in silence,",
    full: `Male love and female love —
two hearts that feel the same storm differently.

A man’s love hides in silence,
but it runs deep — deeper than words can swim.
When he loves, he stops seeing the world —
because to him, she is the world.
He doesn’t compare, he commits.
He fights quietly,
protects fiercely,
and remembers everything he never says.

> “He may not say it every day,
but he builds his world around her — quietly.”

A woman’s love shines openly,
pure, patient, and infinite.
Her love nurtures, forgives, and endures.
She doesn’t just love —
she becomes love itself.
Her heart prays even when her lips are silent.

> “She doesn’t just love him —
she becomes love itself when she does.”

So, who loves the most?
Maybe neither. Maybe both.
Because when love is true,
it stops belonging to genders —
it becomes divine.
Just two souls meeting,
not two roles playing.

> “He loves in silence, she loves in song —
together, they make eternity feel short.”

In the end,
it’s not about who loves the most —
it’s about who stays in love,
who fights for it,
who keeps choosing it, every single day. 💞`,
