    id: 31,
    title: "Not Helpless, But Defined",
    excerpt: "Many times, I wished to ask for help, / but my heart whispered softly — / “Remember, every favor must be returned.”",
    full: `Many times, I wished to ask for help,
but my heart whispered softly —
“Remember, every favor must be returned.”

I’ve learned that
every act of kindness is a silent debt,
a chain that binds the soul,
trailing beyond this lifetime.

Perhaps that’s why
I chose to become strong —
stern, distant, unyielding,
yet inside… just exhausted.

Sometimes I wonder,
if I’m not there to help someone,
does that make me heartless?
Or simply human —
still fighting my own storms.

Each time they say,
“You’re too cold, too harsh,”
I smile quietly,
for they don’t know —
this harshness is my armor, not my wound.

I’ve hidden my tears,
so the world won’t think I’m broken.
I just can’t bear
the pity that comes wrapped as love.

For every help I take
becomes not a bond of care,
but a tether of obligation —
one that holds me across lifetimes.

So I decided —
I need no shoulders to lean on.
If I fall, I’ll rise.
If I lose, I’ll search for victory within.

Maybe that’s why
I refuse to wish for another birth.
For in this one,
I’ve freed myself
from every invisible debt — forever.`,
