    id: 33,
    title: "“The Words That Bled From My Wounds”",
    excerpt: "Someone once asked, / “Why is poetry so important to you?” / I didn’t smile this time—",
    full: `Someone once asked,
“Why is poetry so important to you?”
I didn’t smile this time—
I stayed silent.
Because the answer was buried deep
beneath my ribs.

It’s not just poetry,
It’s the scream
I never wanted the world to hear.

It’s the tears
that hid inside my ink,
so no one could see the pain—
but they could feel it.

Each word crawled out
from the darkness within me,
from the nights I couldn’t breathe,
from the ache I learned to love.

Poetry taught me how to live
before dying completely,
how to rebuild myself
from the ruins of my own silence.

Now when I write,
my words don’t bleed —
they echo.
Echo from the hollow places
that once knew no name.

No, it’s not just poetry —
it’s the unspoken dialogue
between me and my pain,
written in the ink of survival.`,
