    id: 39,
    title: "I once asked my love,",
    excerpt: "“If one day I leave this world, / Will you forget me… / Will you give my place to someone else?”",
    full: `“If one day I leave this world,
Will you forget me…
Will you give my place to someone else?”

He held my face gently and said,
“How could you ever think that, my heart?
Do you trust my love so little
That you ask me such a question?”

Then he took my hand and whispered—
“I promised you forever, remember?
If death takes you away from me,
My shroud will be laid beside yours too.”

But these helpless tears in your eyes,
He said, “Why do they keep breaking me?
Why do you speak of death
As if it’s waiting at your doorstep?”

**Why do your lashes tremble
Under the weight of unspoken fears?
Why do you worry about my funeral
More than your own life?”

Maybe…
Because your love is so deep,
So fierce, so eternal,
That even death cannot separate us.

He told me—
“As long as your breath exists, I am yours.
And when your breath stops…
Even then we won’t part—
Only the world will no longer see us together.”`,
