    id: 59,
    title: "Where My Storm Meets Her Calm",
    excerpt: "She carries sunshine in her smile, / a gentle warmth that lingers awhile. / No need for crowds, no need for noise,",
    full: `She carries sunshine in her smile,
a gentle warmth that lingers awhile.
No need for crowds, no need for noise,
her laughter alone is my favorite choice.

She hides from parties, the endless throng,
yet in my home, she feels she belongs.
Candles and cake, just us in the room,
her presence alone makes shadows bloom.

I am the storm—moody, unsure,
with trust that wavers, and thoughts obscure.
But she is the calm, the steady ground,
a quiet peace where my soul is found.

So sweet, so rare, my dearest friend,
the kind of light that will never bend.
Though storms may come and seasons sway,
her smile will always guide my way.`,
