    id: 68,
    title: "The Villain We Choose to Be",
    excerpt: "Sometimes, I erase the pages / where our laughter was written, / not because they weren’t beautiful,",
    full: `Sometimes, I erase the pages
where our laughter was written,
not because they weren’t beautiful,
but because they keep you from breathing freely.

Sometimes, I wear the mask of the villain,
let you curse my name,
let you believe I was the storm
that broke what we had—
because it’s easier for you
to heal from hate than from longing.

Sometimes, I walk away in silence,
not to escape, not to forget,
but to carve a path where your steps
won’t trip over mine anymore.
I leave so you can move forward,
even if it means I vanish from your story.

And maybe, years from now,
you’ll think of me as the wrong one—
but in that cruel portrait
is hidden the truth:
sometimes love survives best
in the shape of sacrifice.`,
    theme: "",
