    id: 86,
    title: "The Unseen Agreement",
    excerpt: "Life is but an unseen scroll, / Written by God, beyond our control— / A covenant veiled in mist and flame,",
    full: `Life is but an unseen scroll,
Written by God, beyond our control—
A covenant veiled in mist and flame,
Each breath a clause, each step a name.

Like lovers’ vows, fragile yet true,
Some lines are written by me and you.
Our hearts may script what fate withholds,
A secret pact the silence folds.

No ink is spilled, no seal is pressed,
Yet all is signed within the breast.
The stars bear witness, the winds comply,
To bonds unseen, where souls rely.

So walk with me, through night and day,
Our hidden contracts shall not fray.
For life, for love, though blind they seem,
Are both God’s promise—and our dream.`,
