    full: `You were the lone soul
who ever asked me, *How do you fare?*
While I, to the world,
have only inquired *How are you*—
never *Who are you*.

For the measure of a being
is not in the mask they wear,
but in the tremble of their heartbeat.

I see human emotions
without a word spoken—
for my heart, untainted,
feels their unvoiced storms.

If you wish to know
the truest face of a soul,
you must read them in silence,
cradle their spirit in ease—
and only then,
their essence will unfold to you.`,
