    id: 175,
    title: "Complaint to the Stars",
    excerpt: "Why do you shine so brightly, / when you cannot warm me? / Why scatter your silver promises,",
    full: `Why do you shine so brightly,
when you cannot warm me?
Why scatter your silver promises,
knowing they fall into silence?

I asked the night for answers,
but it only gave me echoes—
a thousand lights above me,
none willing to guide my steps.

My complaint is simple:
You dress the sky in beauty,
yet leave the earth in shadows.
Is that not the cruelest gift—
to show us wonder,
but never bring it close?`,
