    id: 192,
    title: "Nature is Truly Singing",
    excerpt: "Birds that echo through the night, / Cool winds drifting, soft and light, / Lightning flares, the raindrops fall,",
    full: `Birds that echo through the night,
Cool winds drifting, soft and light,
Lightning flares, the raindrops fall,
Nature whispers, calling all.

Thunder rolls across the sky,
Leaves awaken, reaching high,
Waves embrace the waiting shore,
Snow descends forevermore.

Droplets fall from trembling leaves,
Streams flow on, a song they weave,
Shadows dance with beams of sun,
Earth and sky now sing as one.

All together, one refrain,
A tender hymn, a sweet refrain—
Within each sound, this truth does ring:
Yes, nature truly learns to sing.`,
