    id: 195,
    title: "Night Itself Is Too Beautiful",
    excerpt: "Who says the night is frightening? / Then they must have never seen its beauty shining. / Have you ever thought—why do we sleep at night?",
    full: `Who says the night is frightening?
Then they must have never seen its beauty shining.

Have you ever thought—why do we sleep at night?
Why work in the day, and rest under moonlight?
Because it’s a tradition, carried for years,
A rhythm of life our heart reveres.

To be honest, only in nights I find my peace,
Each night gives my soul a chance to release.
Even in pain, it is the night that stayed,
It witnessed me broken, weeping, afraid.

The night holds a silence so profound,
If you listen, you hear the softest sound.
The moonlight too gives comfort to eyes,
And some flowers bloom only under dark skies.
Truly, the night has a peace of its own—
A secret beauty, quietly shown.`,
