    title: "A Confession to Goodbye",
    excerpt: "I’ve come to believe / that goodbye is not a wound— / it is a trembling truth",
    full: `I’ve come to believe
that goodbye is not a wound—
it is a trembling truth
we learn only at the edge of love.

Everything that breathes,
everything that shines,
every hand we ever held
was never meant to stay forever.

Stars burn out
not because they fail,
but because their light
has finished teaching the dark.

Years close their doors,
chapters loosen their grip,
and even hearts grow quiet
when they have loved enough.

It breaks us—yes—
to release what once felt infinite.
But in that breaking,
the universe leans closer.

Because every ending
is a soft surrender,
where one life exhales
to let another begin.

We do not disappear—
we change our names,
our forms,
our journeys.

A goodbye, then,
is not an end of existence,
but a beautiful confession:
that something mattered enough
to be complete.

And somewhere beyond this closing line,
a new chapter is already learning
how to breathe.`,
