    title: "Not Incomplete — Just Broken",
    excerpt: "The way you broke my heart, / will fate ever return to you / a love so deep",
    full: `The way you broke my heart,
will fate ever return to you
a love so deep
that it forgets itself
just to stay?

I loved you beyond limits,
and perhaps
that was my only mistake.

They say true love stories
are always incomplete,
but when love exists on both sides,
even incompleteness
doesn’t feel like loss.

Here, love existed—
but only from one side.
Neither did the story become complete,
nor did this one-sided love
earn a name.

If there was no love,
why play the game?
I told you from the beginning—
I don’t have the strength
to love someone again.

Then why did you come close?
Why make my heart
learn your presence
only to leave it shattered?

Was this love,
or just a game?
Was I merely
a toy to pass your time—
picked up when you wanted,
and abandoned
when you were done?

If there was no love,
why come so close?
Why play with my heart,
why break it—
when you never learned
how to stay?

Now there are no questions left,
no complaints—
only a quiet exhaustion
that grows heavier
with every heartbeat.

I asked for love,
not promises,
not a lifetime—
just truth.

But perhaps truth
is the most expensive gift,
one not everyone
can afford.

I no longer wish to stop you,
nor hope for your return.
What has left
no longer belongs here.

I’ve learned this much—
giving your heart
to someone who doesn’t know
how to protect it
is another way
of breaking yourself.

And if you ever remember me,
don’t do it with regret—
remember this instead:
someone loved you
with complete honesty,
and in that honesty
silently broke.`,
