    id: 248,
    title: "When Does a Person Hurt the Most?",
    excerpt: "A person feels the deepest pain / not when they lose something suddenly, / but when what they’ve always longed for",
    full: `A person feels the deepest pain
not when they lose something suddenly,
but when what they’ve always longed for
finally arrives—
only to leave.

It doesn’t just walk away.
It takes the future with it.
It shatters them quietly,
from the inside out.

In that moment,
every reason for living
loses its meaning,
falls apart without a sound.

People say they are lucky.
They point at smiles, at strength, at survival.

But luck has nothing to do with it.
Because no matter how whole they appear,
something essential has already died within them.`,
