    id: 249,
    title: "A Quiet Presence",
    excerpt: "I do not know why it feels this way, / only that it does— / as though something unseen",
    full: `I do not know why it feels this way,
only that it does—
as though something unseen
is always beside me.

A presence that does not announce itself,
yet never leaves.

It knows my needs
before I learn to name them.

It speaks to me
in the spaces where words fall away.

It never mistook my innocence for weakness;
it simply watched me grow.

It feels my tears
before they find my eyes.

It knows me
more deeply than I know myself.

It stands beyond fear,
not as force,
but as calm.

It teaches without instruction,
guides without command—
through awareness alone.

It is the presence
that introduced me to myself.

The presence that held me together
when I was quietly coming apart.

It cannot be seen,
yet it moves with every breath I take.

Perhaps this presence
is not separate from me at all—
perhaps it is what I am becoming,
and what has always been greater than me.`,
