    id: 256,
    title: "HOWL THEORY",
    excerpt: "I want you the way fire wants a forest— / not cruel, just inevitable. / My body recognizes you before my mind can lie.",
    full: `I want you the way fire wants a forest—
not cruel, just inevitable.
My body recognizes you before my mind can lie.

Your voice scrapes me raw.
Your absence stalks the rooms.
I pace. I circle. I do not sleep well anymore.

Love is too polite a word.
This is hunger with a memory.
This is my pulse dragging your name
through every dark corridor of me.

We meet like animals who’ve survived something
and refuse to discuss it.
Our mouths are honest.
Our hands don’t ask permission.

Danger feels holy near you.
I would follow that feeling anywhere—
off the map, past sense,
into the part of myself that still knows how to bite.

If I lose myself here, so be it.
Some instincts are older than fear.
Some happiness comes snarling.`,
