    id: 258,
    title: "Echoes of Rain",
    excerpt: "The rain does not ask permission. / It arrives as memory does — / sudden, soft, insistent —",
    full: `The rain does not ask permission.
It arrives as memory does —
sudden, soft, insistent —
pressing its cold palms against the window.

I have sat in rooms like this before,
listening to water speak in tongues,
translating every knock and pour
into the names lodged in my lungs.

You were the flood I didn't flee.
You were the drought I didn't mourn.
Now rain is just the rain to me —
a sound, a season, not a form.

And yet I leave the window cracked.
I let the damp sit on the sill.
Some doors, once opened, don't go back.
Some echoes linger, ringing still.

----`,
