    id: 278,
    title: "Broken Sides",
    excerpt: "Broken sides are more beautiful than full sides, / they carry the map of storms survived. / Full sides shine only because",
    full: `Broken sides are more beautiful than full sides,
they carry the map of storms survived.
Full sides shine only because
nothing has ever dared to touch them.

The broken ones have learned
how pain sounds at midnight,
how silence presses against the chest
until breathing becomes an act of courage.

Cracks are not empty—
they are filled with memories,
with names once spoken softly,
with goodbyes that stayed longer than they should.

A full side has never questioned itself,
never trembled at its own reflection.
But a broken side has stood there,
shaking, and still chosen to remain.

What breaks also opens.
What opens learns to feel.
And what feels deeply
becomes dangerously alive.

So don’t ask me to be whole again.
I am not unfinished—
I am written in fractures,
and that is where my beauty begins.`,
