    full: `I give my whole heart,
and that is why I tremble at the thought of loving again.
I am tired of learning how to let go.

My mind is a place where words never die.
Every sentence repeats itself,
every careless sound becomes a wound.
So if your love is uncertain,
please do not offer it to me—
I have no strength left for half-hearted affection.

Those I love always leave,
not because I fail to love,
but because my emotions are too deep to be understood.
People think my words are light,
but they sink into my mind
and stay there, quietly breaking me.

I have never truly felt love,
and so I have learned to sit peacefully with my loneliness.
I no longer desire anyone,
because I know how difficult it is
to be accepted with my voice, my feelings, my truth.

Still, somewhere within me,
I am waiting for someone I have never met.
I do not know his name or his world—
only that he feels like a beautiful dream,
a missing piece of my soul.

He will love me more than I love myself.
He will endure my storms,
hold me through my silences,
and never abandon me in my darkness.
He will understand the words I cannot say.

With him, I do not want moments.
I want a lifetime—
every breath, every year, until my last.
Not to be remembered,
but to be chosen, every day.

When I love him, I will love fiercely.
I will fight the world if I must.
I will stand beside him, unshaken.
Because once my heart chooses,
it does not know how to leave.`,
