    id: 311,
    title: "1. (Fear, Dreams & Responsibility)",
    excerpt: "I’m not scared of the dark, / I’m scared of what tomorrow might take from me… / What if I lose my dreams?",
    full: `I’m not scared of the dark,
I’m scared of what tomorrow might take from me…

What if I lose my dreams?
what if my goals slowly fade,
and the fire inside me
turns into silence one day…

Because the truth is—
I don’t just live… I hold on
to my career, my dreams, my poetry,
like they are the only reasons
my heart still beats with purpose.

That’s why I don’t want anyone
to come between me and my path,
not because I don’t care—
but because I care too deeply
about the life I need to build.

I want to give my parents everything,
every smile they never asked for,
every happiness they quietly sacrificed.

So even if I’m tired,
even if I break sometimes—
I’ll still keep walking…
because my dreams
are not just mine anymore.

2. (Mother, Love & Promise)

My mother…
she is a story of silent strength,
a love that never asked to be understood.

She fought for me
from the moment I opened my eyes,
even when the world
was never kind to her.

Yes, she is strict,
yes, she scolds—
but behind it all,
her love holds me together
in ways nothing else can.

And it scares me…
the thought of losing her one day,
because her tears alone
are enough to break me completely.

I wonder sometimes—
why life wasn’t fair to her,
why she had to carry so much pain…

She is the reason I exist,
the reason my world feels alive.

I love her more than words,
more than I can ever show—

I just want to give her everything,
every happiness she deserves,
every moment filled with peace.

And I hope she knows—
even if I’m not perfect,
even if I fail sometimes…

I am trying, every day,
to be someone
she can be proud of. 💫

----`,
