    id: 312,
    title: "“If I Ever Confessed to You”",
    excerpt: "If I ever gathered enough courage to stand before you / and finally tell you what my heart has been hiding… / I think it would sound something like this.",
    full: `If I ever gathered enough courage to stand before you
and finally tell you what my heart has been hiding…
I think it would sound something like this.

I would begin by saying
that loving you was never part of my plan.
You were just someone who appeared in my life—
quietly, unexpectedly,
like a beautiful accident written by fate.

But somewhere along the way
you became more than just a person to me.

You became the reason
my thoughts wander at night
when the world is asleep.

You became the name
my heart repeats silently
like a secret prayer.

And I don’t think you realize
how powerful your presence is to me.

The way you look at me sometimes…
it feels as if the entire universe pauses
just to watch that moment happen.

And when you smile,
it feels unfair to the rest of the world
because no one else gets to see
the way my heart completely melts.

If I were brave enough,
I would tell you that being close to you
does something strange to me.

My heartbeat forgets its rhythm.
My thoughts become soft and reckless.
And suddenly all I want
is to stay a little closer to you.

Closer than what friendship allows.

I imagine simple things—
like sitting beside you in silence,
your hand slowly finding mine
as if it had always belonged there.

Or resting my head against your shoulder
while the world keeps moving around us
without realizing that my entire universe
has already found its place.

And maybe this sounds foolish…

But if love had a home,
I think it would feel like your arms.

If peace had a voice,
it would sound like your laughter.

And if my heart ever chose a place to belong,
it would choose you—
again and again,
without hesitation.

So if one day I ever stand before you
and confess everything I’ve kept inside…

Just know that these words
didn’t appear suddenly.

They were growing quietly in my heart
the entire time
I was falling in love with you.`,
