    title: "In the beginning of my sorrow, a silence was born within me.",
    excerpt: "No thunder announced it, no star bore witness— / yet something sacred within my spirit / quietly turned to ash beneath the weight of existence.",
    full: `No thunder announced it, no star bore witness—
yet something sacred within my spirit
quietly turned to ash beneath the weight of existence.

Once, the world held meaning in its fragile hands,
mountains seemed eternal, oceans merciful,
and the sky a vast scripture of light—
but now their voices pass through me like forgotten prayers.

I have fallen beyond the firmament of the living,
cast from the summit of the highest mountains of being
into the ancient depths where oceans dream in darkness,
where even echoes kneel before the tyranny of silence.

There the great devourers of heaven—black suns of oblivion—
open their endless mouths and drink the light of wandering souls,
and I, a nameless fragment of creation,
drift among their shadows like a broken constellation.

And so I wander through the immeasurable night of the cosmos,
a forgotten verse in the scripture of the universe,
a soul unclaimed by earth, sea, or sky—
lost in the eternal silence before the stars were born. ✨🌑`,
